      "message": "The convention in this repository is to have one TEST or TEST_F for each method/function you are testing.\n\nSometimes the method is not public, so it has to be tested indirectly by calling public methods.\n\nBut please organize your tests so that each TEST or TEST_F covers all the variations for a single method/function.\n\nYou can put blocks of code around each variation so that you don\u0027t run into duplicate local variables.\n\ne.g.\n```\nTEST_F(ManagerTests, Method_Being_Tested)\n{\n    // Test where file is found\n    {\n       ...\n    }\n    \n    // Test where file is not found\n    {\n       ...\n    }\n}\n```",
